text: Gublyukuchukovo () is a rural locality (a selo) in Takarlikovsky Selsoviet, Dyurtyulinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 392 as of 2010. There are 8 streets. == Geography == It is located 4 km from Dyurtyuli, 2 km from Ivanayevo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Dyurtyulinsky District
title: Gublyukuchukovo
